subject: Re: qs-unicode-char-count-proposal.gif
msgSnippet: ... ah, yes.  well, I guess I can t blame it on just being tired.  That was clearly because I couldn t read the scanned version of the QS manual, but still...
messageBody:
> There seem to be a few other typos in this gif:
>
> THEW should be THAW
> AME should be AWE
> OME should be OWE

ah, yes. well, I guess I can't blame it on just being tired. That was clearly because I
couldn't read the scanned version of the QS manual, but still... I should've guessed the
write words, eh?

I made the corrections and updated the graphic.

Can anyone think of letters that are missing from this unicode proposal? more
importantly, does anyone know how to take the next step, of actually FILING a unicode
proposal? I have done some very rudimentary research, enough to know that every
character needs a unique name (thus the proposal), but not enough to know where to go
from here.

oliver
